VoxCeleb.description: -vector) - VoxCeleb is a large-scale speaker identification dataset. It contains around 100,000 utterances by 1,251 celebrities, extracted from You Tube videos. The data is mostly gender balanced (males comprise of 55%). The celebrities span a diverse range of accents, professions, and age. There is no overlap between the development and test sets. It’s an intriguing use case for isolating and identifying which superstar the voice belongs to.
